def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    # Determine if the data object has MultiIndex columns
    is_multicolumn = isinstance(data.columns, pd.MultiIndex)

    if is_multicolumn:
        # If the data has MultiIndex columns, directly unstack it
        unstacked = data.unstack(clocs, fill_value=fill_value)
    else:
        # If not a multi-column, create a dummy MultiIndex for unstacking
        dummy_columns = pd.MultiIndex.from_tuples([(None, col) for col in data.columns],
                                                  names=[None, data.columns.name])
        dummy = pd.DataFrame(data.values, index=data.index, columns=dummy_columns)
        unstacked = dummy.unstack(clocs, fill_value=fill_value)

    return unstacked
